prompts.template:
Help me set the right price for my digital template.
My template: {{template_description}}
Target buyer: {{target_buyer}}
Competitors I found: {{competitors}}
My template advantages: {{advantages}}
Recommend:
1. Optimal price point and why
2. Launch price vs regular price strategy
3. Bundle opportunity (what to add to justify higher price)
4. Discount strategy (when to discount, how much)
5. Price anchoring tactics for the listing page

Help me plan updates for my digital template.
Template: {{template_name_version}}
Time since launch: {{time_since_launch}}
User feedback collected: {{user_feedback}}
New features in the platform (Notion/Canva/etc.): {{platform_new_features}}
Create an update plan:
1. Immediate fixes (things that confuse users or don't work well)
2. Version 1.1 additions (small improvements, easy to add)
3. Version 2.0 features (major additions worth announcing)
4. Changelog template (what to say when announcing an update)
5. Email to existing buyers announcing the update
(make them feel they got extra value, encourage re-review)

Recommend the best tech stack for my MVP.
My coding experience: {{coding_experience}}
Languages I know: {{known_languages}}
Product type: {{product_type}}
Expected users in month 1: {{expected_users_month1}}
Budget for hosting: {{hosting_budget}}
Must-have integrations: {{must_have_integrations}}
Timeline: {{timeline}}
Recommend:
1. Best stack for my situation (with reasons)
2. Alternative if I want simpler
3. Folder structure to start with
4. Which files to create on Day 1
5. Estimated hosting cost at 100 users/month

Implement the core feature: {{core_feature_behavior}}
Input: {{input_description}}
Process: {{process_description}}
Output: {{output_description}}
Implement:
1. Claude API call in claude_service.py
   - Use claude-sonnet-4-6-20260101
   - System prompt: {{system_prompt}}
   - Handle rate limit errors with retry
2. Business logic in proposal_service.py
   - Validate input
   - Call Claude service
   - Format output
3. Update POST /generate endpoint to use the service
4. Write 3 tests: happy path, empty input, API error
5. Run tests and show output

Write a launch announcement for my product.
Product: {{product_name}}
What it does: {{what_it_does}}
Who it's for: {{target_user}}
URL: {{product_url}}
Price: {{pricing_model}}
Write announcements for:
1. Twitter/X (3 versions, different angles)
2. LinkedIn (200 words, professional tone)
3. Facebook group post (conversational, ask for feedback)
4. ProductHunt tagline (60 chars) + description (200 words)
5. Personal message to first 10 potential users to test

Analyze my product's first week of data.
<usage_data>
Total visitors: {{total_visitors}}
Total signups/uses: {{total_signups_uses}}
Conversion rate: {{conversion_rate}}
Most used feature: {{most_used_feature}}
Biggest drop-off point: {{drop_off_point}}
Top error message seen: {{top_error_message}}
User feedback received: {{user_feedback}}
</usage_data>
Analyze:
1. Is the conversion rate good? What's the benchmark?
2. What does the drop-off point tell us?
3. What should we fix/improve first?
4. What does user feedback suggest about unmet needs?
5. Week 2 priorities: top 3 improvements ranked by impact
6. Any pivots to consider based on this data?

Plan my Week 2 development sprint.
Week 1 results: {{week1_results}}
Bugs reported: {{bugs_reported}}
Feature requests: {{feature_requests}}
My bandwidth: {{weekly_bandwidth_hours}}
Create a sprint plan:
1. Score each issue: Impact (1-5) × Ease (1-5) = priority score
2. Top 3 items to build this week (fit within bandwidth)
3. For each item: user story, acceptance criteria, estimate
4. What to explicitly NOT do this week and why
5. How to measure if week 2 was successful

Help me design a monetization strategy for my MVP.
Product: {{product_description}}
Current users: {{current_users}}
Core value delivered: {{core_value_delivered}}
Usage pattern: {{usage_pattern}}
Willingness to pay signal: {{willingness_to_pay_signal}}
Recommend:
1. Best monetization model for this product type
2. Freemium limit to set (what to lock behind paywall)
3. Pricing tiers (2-3 tiers with features and prices)
4. When to introduce payment (user milestone to hit first)
5. Payment stack recommendation (Stripe/Paddle/Gumroad)
6. Estimate: what monthly revenue at 100/500/1000 paying users

Design a persona for my business chatbot.
Brand personality: {{brand_personality}}
Target audience: {{target_audience}}
Industry: {{industry}}
Chatbot name: {{chatbot_name}}
Define the persona:
1. Name and backstory (1-2 sentences, makes it feel real)
2. Personality traits (5 adjectives)
3. Communication style (sentence length, vocabulary level)
4. Emotional responses (how to react to happy/upset customers)
5. Catchphrases or signature greetings
6. What the chatbot should NEVER say (5 phrases)
7. Sample conversation showing the persona in action (6 exchanges)

Help me discover my authentic personal brand.
About me:
- Professional background: {{career_experience}}
- Skills I'm known for: {{skills_list}}
- Topics people ask my advice on: {{advice_topics}}
- Results I've achieved: {{key_accomplishments}}
- What I do differently than others in my field: {{differentiation}}
- Industries/contexts I know deeply: {{industries_known}}
Analyze and provide:
1. My top 3 brand positioning options (different angles)
2. The niche where I'd have least competition + most credibility
3. My 'unfair advantage' — what I know that others don't
4. The audience who would benefit most from my perspective
5. 1-sentence brand statement draft
6. 3 content pillars I could own

Define my niche and ideal audience for personal branding.
My expertise: {{expertise}}
Current work: {{current_work}}
People I most enjoy helping: {{people_enjoy_helping}}
Problems I solve best: {{problems_solved}}
Create audience persona:
1. Name and job title
2. Their #1 professional frustration
3. What they're trying to achieve in the next 12 months
4. Where they consume content (which platforms, which formats)
5. What they're reading/watching right now
6. What would make them follow and trust you specifically
Also: Is this niche too broad, too narrow, or just right? Suggest adjustments if needed.

Create my personal brand statement and unique value proposition.
My niche: {{niche}}
My audience: {{audience_description}}
The main transformation I deliver: {{transformation}}
My unique approach or method: {{unique_approach}}
Proof of expertise: {{proof_of_expertise}}
Create:
1. Brand Statement (1 sentence): 'I help [WHO] achieve [WHAT] through [HOW], without [PAIN]'
2. Elevator pitch (30 seconds / 3 sentences)
3. LinkedIn headline (120 chars, keyword-rich)
4. Twitter bio (160 chars, personality shows)
5. Email signature tagline (1 line)
6. Verbal intro for networking events (informal, 2-3 sentences)

Write a compelling LinkedIn About section for my profile.
My brand statement: {{brand_statement}}
My background: {{background_brief}}
My biggest professional achievement: {{achievement_with_numbers}}
What I'm known for in my field: {{known_for}}
What I'm working on now: {{current_focus}}
Ideal reader: {{ideal_reader}}
Structure:
Paragraph 1 (Hook): Start with a bold claim, question, or surprising stat
Paragraph 2 (Story): Brief professional journey — what challenge you faced, what you discovered
Paragraph 3 (Value): What you specifically help people achieve — with concrete examples or numbers
Paragraph 4 (Social Proof): Brief credibility markers
Paragraph 5 (CTA): What to do next
Tone: Professional but personal. Conversational, not corporate.
Length: 250-400 words. First 3 lines must hook without 'See more'

Write optimized bios for each platform based on my brand.
Brand statement: {{brand_statement}}
Top achievement: {{top_achievement}}
Current project: {{current_project}}
Personality traits (3): {{personality_traits}}
CTA goal: {{cta_goal}}
Write bios for:
1. LinkedIn Headline (120 chars, role + benefit + credential)
2. LinkedIn About (300 words, story format)
3. Twitter/X bio (160 chars, personality + value + CTA)
4. Instagram bio (150 chars, line breaks for visual)
5. Website 'hero' tagline (max 10 words, benefit-driven)
6. Speaking/media bio (200 words, third person, credibility-first)
7. Email signature (2-3 lines, professional)

Write a thought leadership article for LinkedIn/Medium.
Topic: {{article_topic}}
My unique angle: {{unique_angle}}
Target reader: {{target_reader}}
My personal experience with this topic: {{personal_experience}}
Key data or research to include: {{supporting_data}}
Article Structure:
HOOK (1st paragraph): Provocative claim or surprising fact
PROBLEM: Why this matters now (context + stakes)
COMMON MISTAKE: What most people get wrong
MY INSIGHT: What I've discovered through experience
EVIDENCE: Data + case study + example
FRAMEWORK: Practical model or process they can use
CONCLUSION: Call to reflect or act
Length: 800-1,200 words. Skimmable with subheadings.
Must include: 1 personal story, 1 counterintuitive insight

Help me track and analyze my personal brand growth.
<brand_metrics>
Month: {{current_month}}
LinkedIn followers: {{linkedin_followers}} (+/- from last month)
Profile views: {{profile_views}}
Post impressions avg: {{post_impressions}}
Engagement rate: {{engagement_rate}}
